<HEADLINE> Lesotho Remains Cut Off by Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Lesotho today remained cut
off from the rest of the world because of strike by more than 500
Lesotho Telecommunications Corporation (LTC) workers.
</P>
<P>
The strike, started last Wednesday, has completely paralysed
the tiny mountain kingdom's telecommunication system, reported
the South African Press Association.
</P>
<P>
The LTC is the sole provider of all telecommunications
facilities in the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the South African Cellular Phone Company Vodacom
was also unable to operate in Lesotho capital Maseru as its
exchange had been situated on the LTC premises.
</P>
<P>
The striking workers demand improved salaries, better working
conditions and the immediate dismissal or resignation of LTC
Managing Director Lietsiso Mohapeloa.
</P>
<P>
Lesotho is a small land-locked country surrounded by South
Africa. endtiem

