<HEADLINE> Israel Shocked by Foreign Report on Air Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Officers of the Israel Defense
Forces (IDF) said today that they were shocked by the disclosure
of Israel Air Force (IAF) secrets in the latest issue of Jane's
Defense Weekly, Israel Television reported.
</P>
<P>
The prestigious British weekly showed a full map of Israeli
Air Force deployment throughout the country. It not only
revealed the bases, but also the names of squadrons, types
and quantity of the aircraft stationed at each base.
</P>
<P>
According to the weekly, the Israeli Air Force has a
total number of 699 planes and helicopters. It also has a
secret base in Beit Shemesh, which houses Israel's
surface-to-surface long-range Jericho missiles.
</P>
<P>
IDF sources wondered how the authors managed to get their hands
on so sensitive details of the air force.
</P>
<P>
The IAF acknowledged that much of the information is accurate
and potentially damaging. At the same time they noted that some
of the details are out of date and the most tightly guarded
sensitive information still remains top secret.
</P>
<P>
Israel boasts of the most powerful air force in the Middle
East. 
</P>
</TEXT>
