<HEADLINE> Kuwaiti PM Arrives in Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Kuwaiti Prime Minister and
Crown Prince Saad Al-Abdullah Al-Sabah today arrived in Jeddah, a
Saudi Arabian port city, for a one-day visit, the official Kuwaiti
News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The Kuwaiti prime minister held talks with Saudi Crown Prince
Abdullah Ibn Abdul-Aziz on regional and international developments
and bilateral ties, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister, who expected to return home this evening,
also held talks with his Saudi counterpart Crown Prince Abdullah
Ibn Abdul-Aziz after his arrival in Jeddah, where the Saudi Arabia
leaders spend their summer days every year.
</P>
<P>
Their talks tackled regional and international developments,
bilateral ties between the two countries within the framework of
the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) and issues of mutual concern,
the agency said.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister's undeclared visit came three weeks after
an earlier visit.
</P>
<P>
During his last visit, the Kuwaiti prime minister held talks
with Saudi King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz and Crown Prince Abdullah on
boosting joint cooperation and confronting challenges in view of
changes in the regional and Arab arenas. 
</P>
