<HEADLINE> Britain Enters Medal Round Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Jane Sixsmith hit a hat-trick
against Argentina on Tuesday to ensure Britain qualified for the
bronze medal match in the Olympic women's field hockey tournament.
</P>
<P>
Sixsmith's hat-trick and two goals by Mandy Nicholls earned
Britain a 5-0 win over the 1994 World Cup finalists in their final
preliminary round match.
</P>
<P>
They will meet either the Netherlands or South Korea for third
place on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Britain's success represented a fine comeback after they had
lost their first match 5-0 to South Korea.
</P>
<P>
It will be the third successive Olympics that they have played
for the bronze medals. In 1988 they lost at that stage to
Netherlands and in 1992 they beat the South Koreans. 
