<DOCNO> XIE19960731.0026 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UK to Privatize 2,500 Prison Service Jobs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- More than 2,500 jobs in Britain's
Prison Service will be taken over by the private sector under
proposals to privatize information technology in the jail system,
said a local press report today.
</P>
<P>
Under the plans, called Project Quantum, the service's finance,
personnel and inmate records system would be removed from the
public sector and handled by the private sector.
</P>
<P>
The project aims to save 50 million pounds (78 million US
dollars) a year, to cut the Prison Service's 1.6 billion pounds
(2.5 billion dollars) annual budget by 30 percent and to "reduce
head-count."
</P>
<P>
About 100 firms have expressed an interest in the privatization
contract, worth about 150 million pounds (233 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Firms taking over the work are even to be offered office
accommodation in prisons and at Prison Service headquarters in
London.
</P>
<P>
The administration of the Prison Medical Service and of prison
shops may also be privatized. However, services to prisoners by
uniformed staff, medical facilities, education, domestic services
and prison farms and industries are specifically excluded.
</P>
<P>
The report said that if the project goes ahead, it will be the
largest transfer of Prison Service jobs to the private sector, and
it has angered staff who fear that security will be compromised.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
