<HEADLINE> OAU Secretary General Leaves Ethiopia for Arusha, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the
Organization of African Unity (OAU) Salim A. Salim left here
today for Arusha, northern Tanzania, to attend the summit on the
Burundi crisis scheduled for tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
According to an OAU press release, presidents of Kenya,
Uganda, Rwanda and Tanzania as well as the Ethiopian prime
minister are expected to attend the summit.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon, Chairman of the OAU will send representatives to the
summit.
</P>
<P>
Salim said, "We do not expect a Burundi government delegation.
But some elements of political forces in Burundi are expected to
take part in the summit."
</P>
<P>
The heads of state and government during their meeting in
Arusha in June have acceded to Burundi's request for a peace
keeping contingent.
</P>
<P>
Salim said the situation in Burundi has now changed following
last Thursday's military coup that toppled President Sylvester
Ntibantungaya.
</P>
<P>
He said security in Burundi has become a major preoccupation.
</P>
<P>
The leaders will discuss what measures they will take to avert
the worsening situation in Burundi, Salim said, adding that
ending violence and illegality of the coup as well as continuing
past negotiations among the conflicting parties are of crucial
importance to bring about peace in Burundi. enditem

