<HEADLINE> South Korea Urges Japan to Respect Feelings of Neighbors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 29 (Xinhua) -- South Korea today demanded that
Japan respect the feelings of peoples of Asian countries invaded
by Japan during World War II.
</P>
<P>
The demand was made in a commentary released by the South
Korean Foreign Ministry in response to a visit to Yasukuni Shrine
earlier today by Japanese Prime Minister Ryutaro Hashimoto.
</P>
<P>
The Tokyo-based Shinto religious place enshrines the tablets of
Japan's war dead since the 19th century, including seven class-A
war criminals executed at the end of World War II.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that if Japan really wants to establish
good-neighborly relations with the Asian countries which suffered
from the Japanese aggression during World War II, it should
respect the feelings of people of those countries. 
