<HEADLINE> French Foreign Minister to Visit Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 29 (Xinhua) -- The French Foreign Ministry today
confirmed Algerian media reports that Foreign Minister Herve de
Charette will visit that country on Wednesday and Thursday at the
invitation of his Algerian counterpart Ahmed Attaf.
</P>
<P>
The visit, the first by a French foreign minister to Algeria in
three years, is hailed by Algerian media as the beginning of the
normalization of the relations between the two countries,
according to Agence France Presse reports from Algiers.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries have been tense since
Algeria's presidential election in November 1995. Algeria accused
France of interfering its internal affairs by urging the holding
of legislative elections immediately after the presidential
election.
</P>
<P>
France, being Algeria's major aid supplier offering 5-6 billion
francs (1-1.2 billion U.S dollars) each year, is deeply worried
about the spreading of the Algerian Islamic extremism into its own
territory.
</P>
<P>
De Charette is expected to discuss with Algerian leaders the
question of air transportation between the two countries and the
service to be offered by the Algerian national carrier Air Algeria
to some airports in France, according to the AFP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
