<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deng, Qiao Win All-Chinese Final in Table Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 29 (Xinhua) -- Deng Yaping and Qiao Hong won an
all-Chinese affairs here Monday for the top honour in the women's
table tennis Olympic doubles event.
</P>
<P>
The duo of Deng and Qiao, top seed in the world, rallied from a
first set deficit to defeat compatriots Liu Wei and Qiao Yunping
18-21, 25-23, 22-20 and 21-14 at the Georgia World Congress
Center, Atlanta.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal battle also witnessed two pairs of South
Korean paddlers, with Ryu Ji-Hae and Park Hae-Jung becoming the
winners 21-16, 21-8, 14-21 and 21-13 against Park Kyong-Ae and Kim
Moo-Kyo. 
