<HEADLINE> DPRK Suffers Serious Floods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Democratic People's Republic
of Korea (DPRK) has been suffering great losses caused by serious
floods since July 15.
</P>
<P>
Lots of buildings, factories, mines and farmlands are submerged
in deep water, roads and traffics blocked, and power and
telecommunication systems damaged.
</P>
<P>
From July 24-27, continous rainstorms swept many parts of the
country, including Pyongyang, South Pyongan Province, South
Hwanghae Province, North Hwanghae Province, Kaesong, Kangwon
Province, North Pyongan Province and Jagang Province.
</P>
<P>
On July 27, heavy rainfalls in the Tosan County of North
Hwanghae Province reached a record high in history, the Korean
Central News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Measures have been taken by the departments concerned to fight
against the floods and relieve the victims, the agency reported.
