<HEADLINE> Turkey Extends Mandate of US-Led Air Force in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Turkish parliament this evening
approved the renewal of the mandate of the Operation Provide
Comfort (OPC), a U.S.-led allied air force based in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
The parliament agreed to extend the OPC mandate for another
period of five months to the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The pro-Islamic Welfare Party (RP) and the center-right True
Path Party (DYP), two coalition partners, voted for the extension
, while the Democratic Left Party (DSP), the Republican People's
Party (CHP) and the Grand Unity Party (BBP) voted against the
extension. The main opposition Motherland Party (ANAP) did not
participate in the vote.
</P>
<P>
Operating from the Incirlik base in Adana, southern Turkey,
the U.S., British and French fighter planes have been patrolling
northern Iraq since 1991 to prevent Iraqi government troops from
launching attacks against Iraqi Kurds. 
</P>
