<HEADLINE> Ugandan President Meets Buyoya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni
held a meeting today with Major Pierre Buyoya of Burundi who
called on him at Kisozi farm, about 30 km southwest of Kampala.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here this evening said Buyoya came to
Museveni in a capacity of the leader of one of the factions in
Burundi.
</P>
<P>
He made consultations with Museveni on the current situation
in Burundi.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Museveni reiterated his position that all
the factions in the Burundi conflict must go back to the Arusha
agreement reached on June 25, 1996, and use its recommendations
as the basis for finding a solution to the conflict in Burundi.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier meeting with a Burundi delegation sent by Buyoya
to Museveni last weekend, the president indicated that if Buyoya
came to Uganda, he would only be received informally. He made it
clear that Uganda does not recognize the new regime in Burundi.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was also attended by Ugandan Minister of State for
Foreign Affairs in charge of regional affairs Rebecca Kadala.
</P>
<P>
Buyoya, the new Tutsi military ruler, arrived here today to
seek support from Uganda to his military junta which overthrew
Burundi's legal President Sylvestre Ntibantunganya last Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The visit by Buyoya came just a day before a planned African
summit on the Burundi crisis in Tanzania. 
</P>
