<HEADLINE> AL Chief on Resumption of Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the Arab League
(AL) Esmat Abdul Meguid today reiterated the importance of
creating the appropriate climate for the resumption of the peace
process on the Syrian and Lebanese tracks in a way that will
safeguard the full Arab rights.
</P>
<P>
In a statement to the Middle East News Agency following his
tour of France, Lebanon and Syria, Meguid reaffirmed that the AL's
stance reflects the collective Arab will, namely, that peace is a
strategic Arab option provided that it is based on relevant
U.N. resolutions and the land-for-peace principle.
</P>
<P>
On the results of his recent tour of France, Lebanon and Syria,
the AL chief said his visit has achieved the desired objectives.
</P>
<P>
He indicated that his tour took place at the appropriate time,
adding that his talks in Syria and Lebanon were focused on the
activation of the Arab summit resolutions, particularly those
related to the basic principles of the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The AL Secretary General returned to Cairo Monday evening,
winding up his visits to the three countries.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Meguid held talks with political leaders of
the three countries on the current developments of the peace
process in the light of the new changes in the region. 
</P>
