<HEADLINE>   PA Helps Find Body of Israeli Soldier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Palestinian Authority (PA)
has successfully helped Israel locate the body of an Israeli
soldier in south Israel, according to a report of JMCC, a
Palestinian press service based in East Jerusalem, this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
PA President Yasser Arafat told reporters in Bethlehem today
that he had given Israel information on the soldier. Arafat
was in the West Bank city to attend a special meeting of
the legislative Palestinian Council on the issue of Jewish
settlement activity.
</P>
<P>
The body of Ilan Sa'adon, who was kidnaped and killed by
the Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) in 1989, was found
in south Israel earlier today.
</P>
<P>
During his meeting with Israeli Foreign Minister David Levy in Gaza
last Tuesday, Arafat pledged to continue efforts to ascertain
the whereabouts of the remains of Ilan Sa'adon.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, the PA sent its men abroad to find accurate
information about him. They made some contacts with a number of
people concerned and discussed a deal about the matter.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli military authorities are expected soon to make
public the details on how the body was found. 
</P>
