<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Spikers Make Semifinals in Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women spikers routed
their German peers with three-straight sets to secure a semifinal
berth in the Olympic volleyball tournament here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"We have met our goal of entering the last four in the
tournament," said Chinese coach Lang Ping, former ace spiker who
orchestrated her teammates to win five world titles in a row from
1981 to 1986.
</P>
<P>
With the win of 15-12, 15-8 and 15-8, the Chinese nationals
will face the winners of Russia and the Netherlands in the
semifinals.
</P>
<P>
The Germans leapt ahead to lead all the way 6-3, 8-5 and 12-11
with fierce back-court attacks before the Chinese rallied back
through solid blocks over the net and turned over the table to
their merit.
</P>
<P>
Beefed up with the first set victory, the Chinese spikers
sealed the competition without serious challenge from the Germans.
</P>
<P>
"The Germans had a comfortable opening and hindered our
attacks through serves and blocks," admitted Lang Ping who took
the helm of the Chinese national squad one and a half years ago.
</P>
<P>
"With more efforts attained to blocks, we controlled the game
later till the end of the competition," the coach said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
