<HEADLINE> Deadline for Angolan Troops Assembling Extended </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Joint Commission of the
Angloan Peace Process decided today that the deadline for the
UNITA troops quartering will be extended for 15 days to August
15.
</P>
<P>
The move taken by the Angolan joint commission is to ensure
that there will be enough time for all former UNITA soldiers to
gather at assembly points.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the number of the quartered
UNITA soldiers has reached 57,000 by now.
</P>
<P>
During the peace negotiations between the Angolan government
and the UNITA, the former rebel group declared it had more than
63,000 troops.
</P>
<P>
The United Nations special representative based in Angola
Blondin Beye said today that the UNITA generals to be integrated
into the army of national unity will arrive here soon, adding
that the joint commission is satisfied with the result.
</P>
<P>
He also announced that the joint commission will hold a
special meeting to discuss demobilization of surplus
soldiers from either side in Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
