<HEADLINE> Minister Optimistic About Ending Liberian Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's Minister of Information
and Culture Walter Ofonagoro said today he is optimistic that
peace will be restored to Liberia within next year.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with a Liberian delegation in Abuja, capital of
Nigeria, the minister stressed that Liberians need to commit
themselves to regional efforts to resolve the crisis in their
country, according to a television report today.
</P>
<P>
He said the cooperation of all Liberians is critical to the
resolution of the crisis, pointing out that the international
community is becoming impatient with the recalcitrance of some of
the personalities involved in the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that the Liberian crisis has dominated
discussions in the Economic Community of West African States
(ECOWAS) because it is hampering efforts to realize the ideals of
the sub-regional body. 
</P>
