<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-30 19:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Seeks Help to Extinguish Forest Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Turkey today fought with raging
forest fires, as the world responded coolly to the country's
appeal for help.
</P>
<P>
While the fires in Adana, southern Turkey, have been
completely extinguished, the forest fire in the Soke district of
Aydin has been reported to be under control on three fronts,
but it is still continuing on the western front due to strong
winds. The fire has destroyed at least 1,000 hectares of forest.
</P>
<P>
The forest fire near the popular tourist town of Marmaris,
Mugla province, along the Mediterranean coast. It was caused by
negligence during the burning of dried weeds, and is still out of
control on the western front.
</P>
<P>
About 4,000 people are now fighting against the flames in
the region.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, Turkish Foreign Ministry appealed to Israel,
Italy, Spain, Germany, France, Britain and the united States for
help to extinguish the forest fires.
</P>
<P>
Israel has given a positive response to Turkey's appeal and
proposed to send four water tanks, each with a capacity of five
tons, to be installed on helicopters.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has proposed to Britain and the United States on using
the air forces in Incirlik base in Adana. However, both countries
have declined to offer help, saying that the forces were not
appropriate to be used in fire-fighting operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
