<HEADLINE> S.Africa Rejects Refugees' Demands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 30 (Xinhua) -- South Africa today rejected
several demands by African refugees who had protested against the
deportation policy outside the Pretoria office of the United
Nations High Commission for Refugees (UNHCR).
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Pretoria, the Department of Home
Affairs said there was a distinction between the rights of
recognized refugees and those of asylum-seekers and rejected
asylum-seekers.
</P>
<P>
About 300 African refugees staged a demonstration on Monday
outside UNHCR office in central Pretoria, demanding that their
deportation from South Africa be forestalled until they could be
resettled in other countries.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday afternoon, the protesters, who had spent the night
on the pavement in front of the UNHCR office, marched to the
union buildings to present a memorandum to a government official
after police threatened to arrest them.
</P>
<P>
The department said UNHCR would assist refugees or asylum-seekers
to resettle elsewhere only when the current country of asylum was
considered unsafe. 
</P>
</TEXT>
