<HEADLINE> Ghana Set For Elections in December </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Presidential and legislative
elections will be held in Ghana on December 7 this year after
being approved by a parliamentary committee, a radio report
monitored here said today.
</P>
<P>
Political grandstanding has already begun, with finance
minister of the country denying opposition claims that Ghana
faces a financial crisis with external debt surging to seven to
10 billion US Dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, the country's external debt dipped to
4.3 billion Dollars by the end of December last year, including
3.9 billion Dollars of state debt.
</P>
<P>
The total debt compared with 4.5 billion Dollars in 1994 and
4.1 billion Dollars in 1993, the report said, quoting the finance
minister. 
