<HEADLINE> Bomb Threat Forces USAir Jet to Return </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- USAir Flight 894, with 200
passengers and crew members aboard, had to return to the airport
in Philadelphia minutes after takeoff Tuesday night following a
bomb threat, a news report from Philadelphia said.
</P>
<P>
Investigators had not found any bomb and the Boeing 767 took
off again after a four-hour delay.
</P>
<P>
Airport officials said a telephone threat was received 22
minutes after the plane departed for Frankfurt, Germany, at 8:30
p.m. Tuesday (0030 GMT Wednesday). The flight was called back to
land at Philadelphia International Airport and was evacuated
while a search was made. 
</P>
