<HEADLINE> Perry Arrives in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 31 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Defense Secretary
William Perry arrived here today from Saudi Arabia where he
held talks with Saudi government officials on moving U.S. troops
there from urban areas to more isolated remote bases.
</P>
<P>
Perry was rushed to Bayan Palace to meet Kuwaiti Amir Sheikh
Jaber Al-Ahmed Al-Sabah immediately after his arrival.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. embassy in Kuwait declined to give any comment on his
Kuwaiti trip, refusing even to confirm his arrival in the
emirate.
</P>
<P>
A change-of-Command was carried out in the U.S. camp in Kuwait
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Perry arrived in Saudi Arabia Wednesday, where he held talks
with his Saudi counterpart Prince Sultan Ibn Abdul-Aziz.
</P>
<P>
Americans in Saudi Arabia are on a very high state of alertness
following two deadly bombing attacks within seven months in Saudi
Arabia, which killed 24 U.S. servicemen.
</P>
<P>
Five thousand U.S. troops are based in Saudi Arabia
at present. A further 15,000 U.S. military personnel are on duty
elsewhere in the Gulf region. 
</P>
