<HEADLINE> Cyprus' Trade Deficit Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus' trade deficit in the
first three months of this year rose three percent to 303 million
Cyprus pounds (about 606 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to the latest report issued by the Department of
Statistics and Research, total imports rose by 13.5 percent to
459.9 million Cyprus pounds (about 920 million dollars) as
compared with 405.1 million pounds (about 810.2 million dollars)
in the period from January to March in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Total exports amounted to 156.9 million pounds (about 314
million dollars) as compared with 111.2 million pounds (about
222.5 million dollars) in the January-March period, 1995.
</P>
