<HEADLINE> Russia Intensifies Anti-Crime Fight in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian Police has begun
implementing a wide range of measures to fight against crimes in
the entire Moscow region, a source close to the Interior Ministry
said today.
</P>
<P>
National Security Council Secretary Alexander Lebed and Moscow
Mayor Yuri Luzhkov had discussed the measures in details, said the
source, who asked not to be named.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not disclose the details of the measures.
</P>
<P>
More effort to check crime in Russia was part of the
presidential election platform of Lebed, who joined hands with
President Boris Yeltsin after coming third in the first round of
voting last month.
</P>
<P>
As many as 189 crime organizations are operating in the Moscow
region, 30 of which have reached an international scale, according
to the source.
</P>
<P>
These organizations, with approximately 3,500 members, control
about 250 stock companies, more than 600 limited liability
companies and around 40 joint ventures.
</P>
<P>
The criminal groups can hire a professional killer at costs
ranging from 10,000 to 18,000 U.S. dollars, depending on the
importance of the target and the difficulties for the shooter.
</P>
<P>
Police registered 46,671 criminal cases in Moscow in the first
half of the year, with the homicide and rape cases rising 20
percent.
</P>
<P>
Hired killings rose 69 percent compared with the same period of
last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
