<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Macao Government has decided to
donate a total of a million Patacas (about 126,600 US dollars) to
aid victims in recent floods on China's mainland, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Macao Government Information Office announced today that
the donation was decided by Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira as
hundreds of people have died and tens of thousands of people were
left homeless following the severe flooding in central and east
China.
