<HEADLINE> Langkawi International Dialogue Closes in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad today appealed to all nations to distribute their
wealth in a way that will ensure social justice for the people.
</P>
<P>
"We should try new approaches to achieve social justice to
ensure the people have a fair share of the wealth of their
nations," Mahathir said at the closing of an international
dialogue on "smart partnership" in Langkawi, Malaysia, the
Malaysian news agency Bernama reported.
</P>
<P>
It is worth trying "the smart partnership" approach where the
administration, workers and business forged partnerships to
achieve prosperity and stability for the people and countries, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Mahathir also appealed to big corporations to reinvest to
strengthen the process of social justice that will bring more
meaningful purpose for their own existence.
</P>
<P>
Six heads of state, 14 government ministers, as well as many
leading businessmen and government officials from Commonwealth
countries attended the three-day Second Langkawi International
Dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The first Langkawi International Dialogue on Smart Partnership
was held last year.  
</P>
