<HEADLINE> BOC Sets New Record In Deposits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- For the first time the Bank of
China (BOC) is raking in more deposits in RMB than it has loaned.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this past June, the bank's RMB yuan deposits
topped 442.4 billion yuan, eight billion more than the total
amount of loans delivered in the same period, according to an
official of BOC.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the banks deposits in foreign currencies rose by 1.7
billion US dollars, standing at 27.1 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The rising RMB yuan deposits took place and has boosted the
bank's capacity in dealing RMB business, against the backdrop of
the country's promise to make RMB convertible under current items
within this year, along with recent cuts of interest rates.
</P>
<P>
As a move to woo depositors, BOC branches at all levels have
worked without their traditional midday break since July.
</P>
<P>
In the first six months, the bank, as the second largest credit
card issuer in China, issued 3.82 million credit cards to the
public, involving a total of 105.5 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Also the bank recalled a total of 43.6 billion-yuan in overdue
loans in the first five months of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
