<HEADLINE> HK's Dragonair Starts New Service Between HK, Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's major air carrier,
Dragonair, today started operating a new scheduled service from
Hong Kong to Gaoxiong, adding Taiwan to its regional route network
for the first time.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Dragonair said that the carrier will operate 21
flights per week between Hong Kong and Gaoxiong in each direction.
</P>
<P>
This new thrice-daily service is a result of the new commercial
agreement on air services between Hong Kong and Taiwan signed by
Dragonair, Cathay Pacific Airways, Eva Airways and China Airlines
last month.
</P>
<P>
Dragonair is presently operating a network of 23 destinations
covering 14 cities on the Chinese mainland including Beijing,
Changsha, Chengdu, Dalian, Guilin, Haikou, Hangzhou, Kunming,
Nanjing, Ningbo, Shanghai, Tianjin, Xiamen and Xi'an and nine
cities regionally. Starting from August 19 this year it will also
fly to Qingdao. 
