<HEADLINE> Iraq, Iran to Exchange Remains of War Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Iraq said today that it will
exchange the remains of those died in the 1980-1988 war with Iran
in a border zone on August 13.
</P>
<P>
The local newspaper Al-Jumhoriya quoted a source from Iraq's
Foreign Ministry legal department as saying that the Iraqi
authorities will receive 40 bodies of war victims from Iran which
will get 65 in return.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that the exchange of remains of war victims
comes in the framework of the joint minute signed between the two
countries in September 1995.
</P>
<P>
It said that the technical committee in charge of the work is
still searching for the remains of the war victims along the
borders between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Both sides had a similar exchange on June 25 during a meeting
of the joint committee discussing the issue. Iraq handed over 144
Iranian remains while it got 200 from the Iranian side. 
</P>
