<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU's Annual Inflation Falls to 2.5 Percent in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU)'s annual
inflation rate went down to 2.5 percent in June following four
consecutive months at 2.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Figures released today by EUROSTAT, the Statistical Office of
the European Union in Luxembourg, showed that in June the annual
inflation in 11 EU member states was below the EU average.
</P>
<P>
The lowest rate was Finland's 0.4 percent, followed by Sweden's
0.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Greece had the highest rate of 8.8 percent, with Italy next at
3.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
EUROSTAT pointed out that the EU's inflation was lower than the
corresponding rate of 2.8 percent in United States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
