<HEADLINE> UAE to Hold Exhibition on Pharmaceuticals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition on pharmaceuticals
and health care (Arab Pharma 96) will be held in the city of Dubai
in the United Arab Emirates (UAE) from October 12 to 14 this year,
the UAE news agency (WAM) said today.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, the second of its kind, will focus on the
progress made by the UAE pharmaceutical sector, as well as the
need to further health care in the Middle East. The exhibition
will be 30 percent bigger in scale than the first one held in
1994, WAM reported.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the exhibition will include a large number of
major manufacturers and suppliers of medicines and medical
instruments from the U.S., Canada, Britain, France, Sweden,
Greece, Switzerland Syria and the UAE.
</P>
<P>
On the sidelines of the exhimition, an international conference
will be held to discuss modern methods of hospital management. A
large number of doctors, hospital executives, government
officials, pharmacists, manufacturers of medicines, laboratory
assistants, health-care specialists and physiotherapists from the
world will take part, said WAM.
</P>
<P>
The UAE held its first exhibition on pharmaceuticals and
health care in the city of Dubai in 1994, with the participation
of more than 20 states. The medical conference held on the
sidelines of the gathering was attended by more that 250 doctors
and experts from Middle East countries and the Indian
subcontinent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
