<HEADLINE> Thailand, Myanmar to Discuss Border Disputes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Thai Foreign Minister Amnuay
Virawan will visit Myanmar on August 5-6 to attend a joint
commission meeting at which border issues between the two
countries will be discussed.
</P>
<P>
Main problems to be ironed out will include the digging in the
Moei river on the Thai side and the deadlock over construction of
the Thai-Myanmar bridge, said Amnuay, who spoke to reporters when
making an inspection tour of the sites on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Last year Myanmar accused Thailand of illegal encroachment on
the border area, which led to alteration of the Moei river
borderline. Later, Myanmar suspended construction of the border
bridge in June, demanding removal from the reclaimed area of
construction materials, rock filling and all buildings on the
river bank as preconditions for talks.
</P>
<P>
The reclaimed area on the Thai side has since been altered but
Myanmar is yet to agree to resumption of construction on the
bridge.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, Thailand also asked Myanmar to stop planting
stakes along the river and to dismantle concrete barriers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
