<HEADLINE> UN Envoy to Afghanistan to Broaden Contacts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The new UN envoy to Afghanistan,
Norbert Holl, said today that he would broaden his spectrum of
contacts during the peace mission in the war-torn country.
</P>
<P>
Reports coming from Kabul said Holl, who is visiting Kabul,
indicated that he wanted to hear more from those people who do not
belong to the political elite but are intelligent and
sound-minded.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen in the Afghan capital, Holl said that he
would not only talk with Afghan political and military leaders,
but also seek the views of other elements of society, such as
intellectuals, judges and women's groups.
</P>
<P>
Holl, a German diplomat who replaced Mehmud Mestiri as the UN
special envoy to Afghanistan last month, said that he would make
changes to Mestiri's tactics.
</P>
<P>
However, he refused to spell out the details of his peace plan.
</P>
<P>
"I will not be very specific at the beginning of this mission
but I definitely have a few plans and initiatives to get this
process moving again," he added.
</P>
<P>
Holl also stressed that the UN would coordinate its operations
to deal with Afghanistan more closely and that his UN Special
Mission to Afghanistan would remain based inside the war-ravaged
country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
