<HEADLINE> Unidentified Gunmen Kill Three in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Unidentified gunmen opened fire and
killed three people in Abu Quras, Minya province, in southern
Egypt Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Middle East News Agency (MENA) today quoted a
source from the Interior Ministry as saying that the body of Nagih
Abdel Qader Abdel Hamid, 25, was found on a piece of cultivated
land he owned.
</P>
<P>
Also in Abu Quras, Mohsen Badia Gerges, 30, and Ihab Amin
Ghebrial, 35, were shot dead by three gunmen who opened fire at
them and fled afterwards.
</P>
<P>
MENA said that security forces were trying to arrest the
perpetrators of the attacks. It did not give more details.
</P>
<P>
Moslem fundamentalist militants who launched a violent campaign
against the government in 1992 have carried out many terrorist
attacks in Minya.
</P>
<P>
But it was unclear whether Tuesday's attacks were the work of
the Moslem militants, who have attempted to overthrow Egypt's
current secular government and replace it with strict Islamic
rule. 
</P>
</TEXT>
