<HEADLINE> Labour Accidents Increase in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Labour accidents increased sharply
in southern Vietnam in the first six months.
</P>
<P>
Local press said 103 labour accidents happened in Dong Nai
province, southeast of Ho Chi Minh city, during this period as
against 28 cases in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 25 labour accidents occured in Ho Chi Minh city,
causing 25 5 deaths and seriously injuring 12 others.
</P>
<P>
Foreign invested companies were blamed for almost all the
accidents with Teakwang company accounting for 31 cases, press
report said.
</P>
<P>
The accidents were mainly caused by employers's failure to
equip or improve protection facilities and to provide employees
with guidance on labour safety, especially in non-state
sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
