<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Face Up Foreign Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese Communist Party leader Do
Muoi has urged Vietnamese producers to confront strong competition
from foreign firms, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
The party general secretary made his call in a two-week working
trip to the most crucial economic region in the south, including
Ho Chi Minh city and its nearby provinces of Ba Ria-Vung Tau, Dong
Nai, Song Be and Lam Dong.
