<DOCNO> XIE19960731.0137 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Stock Market Surges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Australian stock market rose
sharply after the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) cut official
interest rates today.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index surged 49.5 points, or 2.32 percent,
to 2180.3 points, the highest level since July 11.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index rose by 74.9 points to 3291.6 points,
while the all resources index closed 30.2 points higher at 1338.3
points.
</P>
<P>
The RBA reduced official interest rates from 7.5 percent to 7.0
percent today. Local economists predicted that further interest
rate cuts would come before the end of the year due to a slower
economic growth rate.
</P>
<P>
The interest rate cut helped to lure more funds into the local
stock market, because investors usually move their money from bank
to equity market in pursuit of a higher return when interest rates
drop.
</P>
<P>
Among local shares, BHP jumped 43 cents to 17.03 Australian
dollars, CRA strengthened 41 cents to 18.25 Australian dollars,
National Australia Bank gained 16 cents to 11.74 Australian
dollars, News Corp rose 28 cents to 6.50 Australian dollars and
Gold Mines of Kalgoorlie added five cents to 1.33 Australian
dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover totaled 297.13 million shares, valued at
788.9 million Australian dollars (615.3 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the Sydney Futures Exchange, the September share price index
contract bounced back by 68.0 points to 2199.0 points.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
