<DOCNO> XIE19960731.0138 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Weakens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar weakened
against all major currencies under the impact of official interest
rate cut today.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 77.28 US cents from 78.79 US
cents on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) cut official interest rates
from 7.5 percent to 7.0 percent today. It was the first change of
Australian official interest rates since December 1994.
</P>
<P>
The cut of interest rates and speculations about a possible
interest rate hike in the United States prompted investors to dump
Australian dollars and hedge their funds in other currencies.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar was traded at 83.00 yen against the
Japanese yen at today's close from 84.99 yen yesterday.
</P>
<P>
It was also sharply weaker against the German mark, ending at
1.1376 marks from 1.1663 marks on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Local traders expected the Australian dollar to be under
pressure for some time in the near future, but they said that the
currency was unlikely to fall much below 77 US cents because of
long-term trend of economic growth in Australia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
