<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam to Restore Discipline in Private Health Care Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- An inspection will be conducted
throughout Vietnam in the private health care sector as from
August 1 according to a decision made by the health minister.
</P>
<P>
The inspection will be carried out first in Hanoi and Ho Chi
Minh city before being launched on a nation-wide scale in the
final quarter of 1996.
</P>
<P>
At present, there are over 8,000 private health care
establishments, 2,295 traditional healing establishments, and
7,984 private pharmacies, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
These medical establishments have made contributions to caring
for the people's health. However, they have had shortcomings that
should be eliminated in the near future, officials pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The inspection will focus on evaluating the qualifications of
private medical practitioners, equipment, and the quality of
medicines in order to promote the sector's positive aspects and to
restrict negative effects.
</P>
<P>
Permits to provide private health care services will also be
checked during the inspection.
</P>
<P>
The move is to restore discipline in the private health care
sector as well as in the medicinal market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
