<HEADLINE> Malaysia Detains More Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian police detained 640
suspected drug traffickers during the first half of this year, an
increase of 251 compared to the corresponding period last year,
according to a senior narcotics department official today.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian narcotics department head Salleh Mat Som was quoted
by Malaysia's news agency Bernama as saying the detained drug
traffickers would be charged under the dangerous drugs act which
provided for the mandatory death sentence on conviction.
</P>
<P>
Police seized 125.12 kilograms of heroin and 395,455
psychotropic pills during the period under review compared to
22.39 kg of heroin and 26,915 psychotropic pills in the first half
of 1995, the official said.
</P>
<P>
He said police also seized 799.62 kg of hemp and 1.41 kg of
opium in the first six months of this year, both higher than those
for the corresponding period last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
