<HEADLINE> 50 Exposed to Radiation in Iran's Nuclear Power </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Some 50 people, seven of them
German engineers, were exposed to strong radiation in an accident
at a nuclear power station in Iran's northern Gilan province, the
local Persian-language daily Hamshahri reported today.
</P>
<P>
Among the 50 people, 21 were more seriously injured and were
sent to a hospital nearby after the incident which took place at
the power station, 10 kilometers north of Gilan's provincial
capital city of Rasht.
</P>
<P>
But the daily failed to say when the accident took place and
give more details on the accident.
</P>
<P>
It only said the accident occurred when an Iranian worker picked
up a lost radioactive part from a radiograph machine. He exposed
the others after being in contact with them at the German-built
plant.
</P>
<P>
No official reaction from the Iranian government on the
accident was immediately available. 
</P>
