<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Young Chinese Sturgeon Set Free In Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Researchers in southwest China's
Sichuan Province recently released 30 artificially-bred Chinese
sturgeons in the Yangtze River, in a move to prevent the
extinction of this rare migratory fish species.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese sturgeon, known as the "Living Fossil," is thought
to have lived in the Yangtze River for more than 140 million
years, said a researcher at the Institute of Rare Aquatic Animals
in Yibin city, Sichuan.
</P>
<P>
The sturgeon is under top protection in China.
</P>
<P>
The rare fish used to spawn in the Jinshajiang River, a
tributary of the Yangtze. When they had grown to about 10 cm, they
swarmed to the sea 3,000 km away. As adults, they swam back
upstream to their birthplace.
</P>
<P>
However, their travel route has been blocked by the Gezhouba
Hydro-electric Power Station, which has been in operation for more
than a decade.
</P>
<P>
This is the third time researchers in Yichang have freed the
rare species into the Yangtze. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960731.0160 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Futures Exchange Launches Long-dated Option </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Futures Exchange
(HKFE) launched long-dated Hang Seng Index (HSI) options contracts
today.
</P>
<P>
Ivers Riley, chief executive officer, said that long-dated HSI
options will provide investors with an additional investment and
hedging tool, complementing the existing HSI options contracts.
</P>
<P>
The contract specifications for long-dated and short-dated HSI
options are the same except in their contract months and strike
prices.
</P>
<P>
In contrast to short-dated HSI options which have a maximum
term of 12 months, long-dated HSI options have expirations of up
to 24 months. If the residual term of long-dated HSI options is 12
months or less, they are integrated into the cycle of short-dated
HSI options.
</P>
<P>
Riley said that since the launch of the current short-dated HSI
options contracts in March, 1993, trading volume has been growing
steadily, adding that this highly encouraging trend is another
factor for the introduction of long-dated options.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, the average daily turnover for HSI options was 1,426
contracts. In 1994 and 1995, the volume increased to 2,446 and
2,614 contracts respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the volume further surged to
3,843 contracts per day.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
