<HEADLINE> Japan Provides Grant Assistance for Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Japanese government will
provide a total of 681.3 million rupees (19.5 million U.S.
dollars) in grant assistance for Pakistan's Mother and Child
Health (MCH) Center and as a debt relief for the country,
according to an agreement signed here today.
</P>
<P>
Japanese Ambassador to Pakistan Takao Kawakami and Javed Talat,
secretary to the Pakistani government in charge of the Economic
Affairs Division, signed the agreement.
</P>
