since China's world champion Tan Shuping failed to qualify for the
semifinals Tuesday night. European champion Vera Ilyina of Russia
and Anna Lindberg of Sweden now lead the 18 top finishers after
five preliminary dives.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine's world record holder Inessa Kravets is the one to beat
in the women's triple jump final, American Gail Devers and
Sweden's Ludmila Enquist are top favorites in the 100m hurdles,
while Jamaica's Deon Hemmings and Germany's Silvia Rieger may
fully extend American world record holder Kim Batten in the 400m
hurdles final.
</P>
<P>
Kenya's David Kiptoo and Fred Onyancha are expected to vie for
the men's 800m title with Norberto Tellez of Cuba and Benyounes
Lahlou of Morocco. World record holder Juergen Schult of Germany
will face serious rivals from Russia, Hungary and Lithuania in the
discus throw final.  
</P>
