<HEADLINE> Nigerian Customs Revenue Up 51.9 Percent in Six </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Nigeria customs service
announced that it realized about 22.81 billion Naira (2.7 billion
US Dollars) in the first six months of this year, an increase of
51.91 percent from one year earlier.
</P>
<P>
The big growth shows the services have beefed up revenue
collection machinery, the customs said.
</P>
<P>
A target of 60 billion Naira (7.1 billion Dollars) has been
set for the whole year as against last year's 35 billion Naira
(4.1 billion Dollars).
</P>
<P>
The customs said on Tuesday the 22.81 billion Naira figure did
not include a 32.41 billion Naira (3.8 billion Dollars) revenue
collected by the service on behalf of some government agencies
for the period under review.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown of the figure shows 16.6 billion Naira (1.95
billion Dollars) was realized from imports while 5.32 billion
Naira (62.6 million Dollars) came from excise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
