<HEADLINE> China Plans Flower Producing Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- China's flower industry will
blossom in the next two years, with help from a multi-million
dollar project in southwest China's Yunnan Province that will
produce 30 million high-quality flowers and plants every year.
</P>
<P>
"It is one of China's major steps China to speed up the
development of seedlings of flowers and plants," officials from
the State Planning Commission said.
</P>
<P>
Currently, a large number of fresh and quality flowers are
imported. The disorderly and unsystematic imports, low quality,
plant diseases and insect pests are major obstacles in the
country's development of its flower industry, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The new project, with an investment of 36 million yuan, will be
built by the Yunnan Jingyun Co. and the Yunnan Gardening High-Tech
Development Co.
</P>
<P>
It will focus on studying the key techniques, facilities and
standardization of flower seedling production, and on the
development of new breeds that will meet the demands of the
overseas and domestic markets.
</P>
<P>
Modernized facilities will also be built for virus detection,
anti-diseases, anti-insect-pests and storage of fresh flowers.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to be completed in two years, the
officials said.
</P>
<P>
China's flower and plant growing area is totaled 75,000
hectares, and its flower exports amount to 60 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the planning commission, the annual growth rate of
flower production and export is expected to reach 10 percent.
</P>
<P>
The current world flower sale is about 100 billion US dollars
and is expected to reach 200 billion by the end of the century.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
