<HEADLINE> Jiangsu Completes Grain Purchase Quota </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangsu Province has
put in storage 1.75 billion kg of grain by July 25, completing the
central government's grain purchase quota for the summer.
</P>
<P>
The province had also purchased 900 million kg of grain at
market price, 500 million kg more than during the same period in
1995.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu, located at the lower reaches of the Yangtze River,
reaped 12.01 billion kg of summer grain, 11.9 percent more than in
last year's corresponding period.
</P>
<P>
The grain was harvested despite severe flooding that ravaged
much of the province.
</P>
<P>
Since early June, heavy floods in Jiangsu have affected more
than three million people, causing 56 deaths by July 18. The
floods damaged over 800,000 ha of crops, and 49,000 ha were
unsalvageable. 
</P>
</TEXT>
