<HEADLINE> Stop Soil Erosion, Museveni Urges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- President Yoweri Museveni has
called for planting more trees to stop soil erosion and silting
of water bodies, "the New Vision" paper reported today.
</P>
<P>
In a speech read by Premier Kintu Musoke when launching the
national environment action plan and the national environment
management authority on Tuesday, Museveni urged people "to ensure
that trees and other appropriate vegetation cover are planted on
all banks of rivers, lake shores and tops and slopes of bare
hills."
</P>
<P>
Soil erosion causes serious siltation of water bodies
including lakes, rivers and streams in Uganda. For instance, Lake
Victoria has gone down as much as two meters due to soil erosion.
</P>
<P>
In order to mitigate possible adverse effects from the growing
industries, the president ask the parties concerned "to conduct
environment impact assessments and also build into their
processing efficient effluent management and disposal systems."
</P>
