<HEADLINE> Adult Education Popular In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The popularity of adult education
is growing along with the booming economy in China's largest
industrial and commercial city as local residents desire to extend
their knowledge of science, technology, and culture.
</P>
<P>
The number of people attending adult education classes amounted
to 2.5 million by the end of June, a rise of 23.6 percent over the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai had 101 adult education schools, 122 adult polytechnic
schools, and 255 township-run cultural and technological
schools. The number of adult education departments at other
institutions exceeded 1,000.
</P>
<P>
More than 400,000 local officials and professional technical
workers have attended classes in recent years. Most have gotten at
least one graduation certificate after having learned an
additional skill.
</P>
<P>
Many local enterprises are also placing importance on personnel
training at all levels.
</P>
<P>
The Baoshan Steel Complex has provided training for more than
2,300 college graduates over the past several years, and has been
working in cooperation with a dozen colleges and universities,
inviting well-known professors to give lectures to its employees.
</P>
<P>
Figures show that Shanghai now has 970,000 technical personnel,
or only some 700 for every 10,000 residents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
