<HEADLINE> Highway Robbers Sentenced to Death in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Nine criminals found guilty of
robbing people along inter-province highways in three Chinese
provinces have been sentenced to death, today's "People's Daily"
reported.
</P>
<P>
In announcing the death sentences, the Supreme People's Court
said restoring order along inter-province highways is one of the
goals of a three-month crackdown on crimes.
</P>
<P>
Three farmers from south China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region reportedly placed axe heads on inter-province highways in
Guangxi and Hubei provinces to stop 14 cars, and later robbed the
drivers and passengers. The thieves took more than 100,000 yuan
from 45 people during the last four months of 1995.
</P>
<P>
In east China's Zhejiang Province, three local farmers used
guns, knives and axes to stop eight cars, and then made off with
60,000 yuan in cash, watches, jewelry, and leather clothing from
more than 60 people, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
Another three criminals robbed passengers traveling on
long-distance buses in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province by
spiking victims' drinks with drugs.
</P>
<P>
They managed to steal more than 500,000 yuan from the
passengers before being apprehended in January 1995, said the
paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
