<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rebels Massacre 60 in N. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The rebels of the Lord's
Resistance Army (LRA) killed more than 60 civilians on Monday and
lined 18 bodies along a main road at Gulu district in northern
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
It is one of the most gruesome incidents of the nine year-old
insurgency in northern Uganda, reported "the Monitor" newspaper
today.
</P>
<P>
Before the killing, the rebels torched hundred of houses in
"punishment" on the locals for allegedly frustrating their war
efforts against the government troops.
</P>
<P>
The killings took place in Kilak areas of Parabongo, Pabbo and
Palwong about 40 kms along the Gulu-Juba highway, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
It added there are fear that the death toll could even be
higher.
</P>
<P>
The LRA was founded in April 1987 by Joseph Kony, a
32-year-old former catechist in Catholic parish, after he fell
out with the Catholic church. 
</P>
</TEXT>
