<HEADLINE> Russia to Launch Eurobond This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia will make an important step
towards entering the international financial market by launching
its first Eurobond by the end of this year, a top Russian
financial official said today.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with 80 German members of the 600-strong London
Club of commercial bank creditors, Russian Deputy Finance Minister
Mikhail Kasyanov said the bond, the first of its kind since before
the 1917 Russian Revolution, will be denominated in dollars.
</P>
<P>
The minister did not tell how much Russia expected to raise
with the bond, but previous suggestions from the country's finance
ministry have indicated an issue volume of about 300 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed confidence in the International Monetary Fund
on transferring the regular monthly installment for a
10-billion-dollar loan by August 14 to aid Russia's transition to
a market economy.
</P>
<P>
Russia has attempted to launch the bond earlier, but it was
delayed by the presidential election last month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
