<HEADLINE> More Foreign Investment In China This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- China approved 12,464
foreign-funded enterprises in the first five months of this year,
with a combined contractual value of 40.6 billion US dollars, 67
percent more than the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Overseas funds used totalled 15.3 billion US dollars, a rise of
27 percent, the overseas edition of "People's Daily" quotes Wang
Liaoping, deputy head of the Foreign Investment Department of the
Ministry of Foreign Economic Relations and Trade, as saying.
</P>
<P>
More than 270,000 foreign-funded firms have been built in
various parts of China since the country began its economic
reforms 18 years ago. There are now 121,000 foreign-funded firms
operating in China.
</P>
<P>
The industrial output value generated by these enterprises
accounted for 14.5 percent of the national total, while their
imports and exports in the first five months amounted to 47.8
billion US dollars, a 28-percent increase over last year's period.
</P>
<P>
Because of improvement in the investment environment in
central and western parts of China, the amount of overseas funds
coming to these areas saw a 24-percent rise, higher than the
national average growth rate, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that the Chinese government has been working on
policies on the use of foreign funds in central and western parts
of the country for the next five years. The government will grant
preferential treatment to those who invest in capital cities,
development zones, and high-tech zones in those parts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
