<HEADLINE> Romania, U.S. Agree on Co-Production of Helicopter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Romanian government today
signed a memorandum of intent with a U.S. firm to jointly produce
helicopters with both military and civilian capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The document calls for the co-production of Cobra helicopter
designed by the U.S. Bell Helicopters Textron.
</P>
<P>
Romanian Defense Minister Gheorghe Tinca and the U.S.
manufacturer's president, Lewis Campbell, signed on the memorandum
at a ceremony held at the Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Tinca said that Romania, after two years of study, chose Cobra
as its production partner because its military needs attack
helicopters and that the project will help Romania's aircraft
industry survive.
</P>
<P>
Cobra attack helicopters are now widely used in the
U.S. military. But they also have civilian capabilities and
Romanian hoped that the U.S.-Romanian production of helicopters
for civilian purpose will help open up the eastern European market.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Romanian President Ion Iliescu earlier today,
Campbell told his host that he would like to see the co-production
project finalized by the end of September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
