<HEADLINE> Indian Government to Further Cut Fertilizer Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government is
considering to further cut fertilizer prices for small farmers as
part of its measures to raise agriculture production.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture minister Chaturanan Mishra has mooted a plan to
provide additional concession on fertilizer prices with the
cooperation of the fertilizer industry, an official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Agriculture Ministry is also considering ways and means of
bringing down the cost of seed to enable farmers switch over to
better crop varieties. The high cost prevents them even from
renewing the seed of the existing varieties, the official said.
</P>
<P>
"Hunger cannot be banished unless the small and marginal
farmers are helped to reap bigger and better harvests," the
official quoted the agriculture minister as saying.
</P>
<P>
In the new budget tabled to the parliament here on July 22,
Finance Minister P. Chidambaram emphasized the importance of
agriculture development and listed measures the government would
take to encourage farmers for rapid agriculture progress.
</P>
