<HEADLINE> IDB Launches $200 Million Bond Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today launched a 30-year bond issue of 200 million
U.S. dollars in the U.S. domestic market.
</P>
<P>
Priced at 99.9786 percent, the issue matures on August 1, 2026,
and has semi-annual coupon of 6.95 percent. The re-offer spread is
seven basis points over the comparable U.S. Treasury bond.
</P>
<P>
Morgan Stanley &AMP; Co. is the lead manager and underwriter of the
issue.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds will be incorporated into the IDB's ordinary
capital and will be used to help finance the economic and social
development of the Bank's 25 Latin American and Caribbean member
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
