<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Police Round Up Rebel Suspects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police and security
forces have rounded up 220 Tamil rebel suspects in a combined
search operation in Colombo since Sunday, security sources here
said today.
</P>
<P>
The suspects had come to Colombo from Jaffna in the North and
Batticalao in the East to go abroad for employment, according to
the sources.
</P>
<P>
However, earlier intelligence reports said several LTTE
(Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam) cadres had infiltrated Colombo
to target key installations and VIPs, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The reports were confirmed when the rebels blasted a train at
Dehiwala near Colombo, killing over 70 people and injuring over
500 others on July 24.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan police has tightened security in and around the
capital city of Colombo since last Sunday to prevent possible
Tamil rebel attacks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
