<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Triumphs Over U.S. in Women's Handball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- China triumphed over the United
States with a final score of 31-21 at the pool A women's team
handball match at the Georgia World Congress Center here today.
</P>
<P>
With the victory, China will play Germany of pool B for the
fifth place in the classification round scheduled for August 1.
</P>
<P>
China's Zhai Chao scored 11 points alone for the Chinese team,
while her teammate Shi Wei added another nine goals to hand the
U.S. team a resounding defeat.
</P>
<P>
"The United States were quite nervous today, their players
didn't have a lot of experience, so when the game was close they
got nervous," said Han Naiguo, head couch of the Chinese team.
</P>
<P>
China and the United States traded goals in the beginning of
the game. But China had a winning streak after 10 minutes into the
first half, scoring eight points in a run to lead the United
States 14-7 with four minutes left in the first half.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the Chinese players increased their lead to
25-15 in the first 15 minutes, as they continued to outscore the
nited States. The United States had two short winning streaks in
the rest of the game. But China maintained its lead, finishing the
game with a score of 31-21.
</P>
<P>
"We gave them the game," said Claes Hellgren, head coach of the
U.S. team. "This was a game we should have won. We have to play
our way, stay with our own game. We can't play their game."
</P>
<P>
After losing to China, the United States will face Angola of
pool B to vie for the seventh place.
</P>
<P>
"We have to win the game for pride," Hellgren said of the
coming battle with Angola. 
</P>
</TEXT>
