<HEADLINE> Uruguayan Navy in "Unitas" Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan Navy's Artigas
frigate will take part in the second stage of the "Unitas 37"
naval exercises to be held next week in Brazilian waters.
</P>
<P>
The Uruguayan presence is limited to one surface ship and an
aircraft, because of budget problems.
</P>
<P>
Units from the Navies of Argentina, Brazil, the United States,
and Uruguay will participate the second and the third stages of
the operation. The third stage will occur in Uruguayan waters
starting August 24.
</P>
<P>
The first Unitas operation was held in 1960 and since then the
Uruguayan Navy has participated with surface, air, and land
units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
