<HEADLINE> China, Russia, Cuba and Brazil Reach Olympic Semi-finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- China meet Russia and Cuba take on
Brazil in the Olympic women's volleyball semi-finals after they
beat their respective opponents in the quarter-finals Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese team, which placed seventh in the Barcelona
Olympics, beat Germany 15-12, 15-8 and 15-8 to move into the
semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
"We are very happy to reach the semi-finals," said Chinese
coach Lang Ping.
</P>
<P>
Germany led early in the first set at 6-3, 8-5 and 12-11, but
China made up the margin and dominated the match thereafter.
</P>
<P>
"China's defence and offence beat our team, and we had some
trouble in blocking," said German coach Siegfried Kohler.
</P>
<P>
Russia, silver medalists of the last Olympics, rallied to beat
European champions the Netherlands 10-15, 15-7, 15-9, 15-10.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch team launched fast attacks and forced their Russian
opponents into frequent errors. The Dutch team win the first set
15-10.
</P>
<P>
But the Russian team took over the domination in the second set
with fierce attacks and tight blocking.
</P>
<P>
"We made several adjustments but can't halt the Russians," said
Bert Goedkoop, coach of the Dutch team, "Our players were nervous
in the game."
</P>
<P>
Asked the chances for the Russian team to win the semi-final
match, Kappol said: "We are capable of beating the Chinese team."
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Cuba, which only placed third with a slow
start in the Pool B preliminaries, denied the Americans' hope for
a semi-final berth as they trounced the hosts 15-1, 15-10, 15-12.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilians, cheered by their fans in yellow T-shirt at Omni
Coliseum, scored a straight set win of 15-4, 15-2 and 15-10 over
South Korea.
</P>
<P>
South Korea dropped into the classification round and will play
the United States on Wednesday, while the Netherlands take on
Germany. The winners of the two matches will play for the fifth
place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
