<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar, Thailand to Designate Border Checkpoints </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 31 (Xinhua) -- High ranking officials of Myanmar
and Thailand are due to hold a meeting here today on designating
checkpoints on the Myanma-Thai border, according to diplomatic
sources.
</P>
<P>
An eight-member Thai delegation, led by director of Asian
Affairs of the Foreign Ministry of Thailand Suvidhya Simaskul,
arrived here Tuesday to attend the meeting on border checkpoints.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the 13th meeting of the Myanmar-Thailand Joint
Boundary Commission was held in Thailand. Two Myanmar regional
commanders, Southeastern Commander Major-General Ket Sein and
Eastern Commander Major-general Tin Hlut, attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
During Thai Prime Minister Banharn Silpa-Archa's official visit
to Myanmar in March this year, Myanmar reopened three border
checkpoints on the Myanma-Thai border at Tachilek-Maesai,
Kawthaung-Ranong and Myawaddy-Maesot, and the two sides signed an
agreement to work out ways and means to synchronize the procedures
and practices on border crossing at respective border checkpoints.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
