<DOCNO> XIE19960731.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuban scientists Invent Biological Substances to Kill </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Three Cuban scientists are
carrying out new experiments with a substance they invented called
Griseleaf, which can kill mosquito larvae in 72 hours.
</P>
<P>
Griseleaf has already been successfully tested in the fight
against malaria-carrying mosquitoes, Cuban Public Health Ministry
representative Grisel Montero said.
</P>
<P>
Tests are also being carried out on another product as
effective as Griseleaf to combat the anopheles mosquito that
transmits the organism which causes some 23 diseases including
dengue, a tropical disease causing joint pains, fever and rash.
</P>
<P>
The scientists said the World Health Organization (WHO) is
working with these kinds of products as part of the biological
fight against illnesses caused by the "Aedes aegypti" and the
"Albopictus" mosquitoes.
</P>
<P>
"Griseleaf is effective for the elimination of the anopheles
and culex mosquitoes and other vectors of the encephalitis
bacterium. It does not affect people, wildlife and plants, and
does not pollute the environment," an Cuban expert said.
</P>
<P>
Mosquitoes in Central America have become resistant to many
chemicals because of the indiscriminate use of insecticides which
also damage the regional ecosystem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960731.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Formation in World Weightlifting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- With the emerging of Chinese
lifters in the world and 15 new world records set at the Olympic
Games, the sport of weightlifting has entered a new era.
</P>
<P>
After ten-day competition, China collected two golds to share
the lead with Turkey, Greece and Russia in the team standings. It
is the first time in 12 years that China displayed its power on
the Olympic weightlifting arena.
</P>
<P>
"China tells the world through the Olympics its power in
weightlifting," said International Weightlifting Federation
spokesman Jeno Boskovics. "I should say that China is a challenge
to other weightlifting powers in the world."
</P>
<P>
After Tang Lingsheng opened the gold account for China in the
59-kg category, Zhan Xugang added one title in the 70-kg division
with three world records.
</P>
<P>
Zhan Xugang is among of the lifters who collected five gold
medals for China at the last World Championships in November of
1993.
</P>
<P>
Apart from China, Turkey, Greece and Russia each also had two
golds in the ten-category competitions.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Naim Suleymanglu, who was once called as "Pocket
Hercules", became the first lifter to win the gold medal in
consecutive three Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
After shining in Seoul and Barcelona, Suleymanglu continued to
dominate the 64-kg category in Atlanta, winning the title with one
world record in the total.
</P>
<P>
Akakide Kakhiashvilis of Greece, who competed for Georgia in
Barcelona four years ago, deserved a special mention.
Kakhiashvilis not only won the 99-kg category, one of the golds
for his new country, but also broke the old world record in the
jerk by seven kilograms.
</P>
<P>
"It is a huge margin, it is the first time in weightlifting's
100 year history," said Boskovics. "It is a record of the world
record."
</P>
<P>
At the year 1993, the International Weightlifting Federation
changed ten categories, in aim to clean its name as drug-abused
sport. The change has resulted in a record-broken wave at the
Centennial Olympics Games. According to statistics, a total of 15
world records have been rewritten in the past ten days.
</P>
<P>
"We have never experienced so many exciting moments in
weightlifting competition before," Boskovics said. "The results
are fantastic, the crowds are supportive and the competition is a
success." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960731.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Province Increases Data Communications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province has raised its
annual investment in data telecommunications to 400 million yuan
and built a province-wide data web involving the country's biggest
financial network.
</P>
<P>
The province expanded its network for DDN (digital and data
network) and Internet services in 1995, adding 9,000 and 13,000
accesses to its packet exchange and DDN networks, respectively,
bringing combined switching capacity to 34,000 terminals,
according to China Electronics News.
</P>
<P>
With 10,000 subscribers, the Internet service now is available
in all the cities and counties in the province , the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The expansion of the packet exchange network used Pass Port
machines from Northern Telecom, a leading Canadian telecom
business, and AT&AMP;T's DACS II for the DDN project.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's financial network, which was completed in 1995, now
has more than 1,000 automatic teller machines linked, the largest
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong plans to develop wireless data telecom systems in the
Pearl River Delta, the richest region of the province, and other
booming coastal areas over the next five years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
