<HEADLINE> Croatia Upset by Australia in Men's Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Olympic silver medalist Croatia
was eliminated out off the top-four at the men's basketball
quarterfinals here Tuesday, going down to the sharp shooting
Australia 73-71.
</P>
<P>
Australia entered the semifinals and will take on the winner of
the other quarterfinal match between the United States and Brazil
while Croatia had to play for the fifth to eight positions.
</P>
<P>
Andrew Gaze led the Australian scores with a game high 26
points and Tony Ronaldson added 17. The duo also hit 8 of
Australia's 11 three-pointers.
</P>
<P>
Croatia was headed by Vladan Alanovic with 18 points and Stojan
Vrankovic added 16. NBA champion Chicago Bulls' guard Toni Kukoc
was finished with 13 points and 9 rebounds but Boston Celtics'
center Dino Radja came out with an empty hands both on the board
and scorings.
</P>
<P>
Croatia played without its injuried shooting guard Arijan
Komazec and failed to make any shot from the 3-point rang in 15
minutes to trail 34-18 behind.
</P>
<P>
The taller Croatians' inside attacks cut the dificit to just 5
points in the dying minute of the first half. But Gaze poured in
all his three throws on the line to widen it to 41-33.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, the Croatia almost took over the contral
but Kukoc missed all his baskets in the final three munites to
allow the Aussies walked away with the biggest surprise since in
the Olympic basketball tournament started in July 20. 
</P>
</TEXT>
