<HEADLINE> Serb Delegation Presses for Indictment of Izetbegovic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A Bosnian Serb delegation today
met with Yugoslav war crimes tribunal prosecutors to press for the
indictment of Bosnia's Muslim President Alija Izetbegovic.
</P>
<P>
But neither delegation leader Igor Pantelic or tribunal deputy
prosecutor Graham Blewitt gave details of the talks this morning,
according to reports reaching here from the Hague.
</P>
<P>
The Serb delegation and the United Nations court are expected
to issue a joint statement when the talks end either Wednesday or
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Pantelic, together with Bosnian Serb justice minister Marko
Arsovic, arrived in the Hague on Monday for a visit that seems to
indicate some improvement in relations between the Bosnian Serbs
and the tribunal.
</P>
<P>
Last week, Arsovic said he would press for the indictment of
Izetbegovic, claiming Bosnian Serbs had sent the tribunal
documents supporting their call. But he did not give details of
the documents or the nature of the charges.
</P>
<P>
The delegation also plans to visit Bosnian Serb Dusan Tadic,
who is on trial for war crimes and crimes against humanity carried
out during the nearly four-year war in the former Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
"Mr. Tadic is a Bosnian Serb citizen so we are going to visit
him this evening," delegation leader Igor Pantelic said.
</P>
<P>
A 40-year-old former cafe owner from northwestern Bosnia, Tadic
has pleaded innocent to all 31 charges against him, including
those accusing him of visiting three Serb-run camps in
northwestern Bosnia in 1992 to kill and torture Muslim inmates.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19960731.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1996-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Champion Eliminated in Women's Springboard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- World champion Tan Shuping of
China suffered a surprising elimination in the preliminary of the
women's springboard here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Tan, gold medalist at th 1994 World Championships and one of
the title favorities at the Centennial Olympics, started the
prelimnary well but faltered in her third and fifth dives. She
placed a lowly 23rd in the 30-diver preliminary and was
eliminated.
</P>
<P>
The top 18 divers from the 5-dive preliminary qualify for
Wednesday's semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
It was Tan's second early elimination at Olympics. At the 1992
Barcelona Olympic Games, Tan was also eliminated in the
preliminary phase and finished only 17th.
</P>
<P>
Tan's teammate Fu Mingxia, who won the first diving medal at
the Atlanta Games, finished fourth at 284.28. She will count on
herself to keep the gold for China in Wednesday's final.
</P>
<P>
China won the gold medal of the event in the previous two
Olympic Games through "Diving Queen" Gao Min.
</P>
<P>
European champion Vera Ilyina of Russia won the preliminary
with a total of 308.88 points. Anna Lindberg of Sweden finished
second at 292.02 and Olena Zhupyna of Ukraine ranked third at
286.47.
</P>
<P>
The top 18 divers from the preliminary will take a 5-dive
semi-final round on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
