<HEADLINE> Australia Beats Croatia in Men's Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Tony Ronaldson scored four points
to help Australia beat Croatia 73-71 in the men's basketball
quarterfinal here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The victory advances Australia (5-1) into Thursday's semifinals
against the winner of the match between the United States and
Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Mark Bradtke of Australia tied the game 66-66 with two free
throws with 1:25 left. Toni Kukoc missed on a drive to the basket
with 58 seconds left on the game clock and five on the 30-second
shot clock.
</P>
<P>
Australia worked the shot clock down and Ronaldson let fly from
right in front of the Croatia bench and was fouled by Dino Radja,
who plays for the Boston Celtics. Ronaldson made the free throw to
complete the four-point play.
</P>
<P>
Slaven Rimac of Croatia missed badly on a 3-pointer with 20
seconds left and Australia made three of four free throws around a
dunk by Rimac with 11 seconds left for a 73-68 lead. Vladan
Alanovic of Croatia hit a 3-pointer with three seconds left for
the final margin.
</P>
<P>
Andrew Gaze led Australia with 26 points and Ronaldson finished
with 17 points.
</P>
<P>
Alanovic led Croatia with 18 points while Stojan Vrankovic
added 16 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
