<HEADLINE> Germany to Finance 52 Million Marks Palestinian Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Germany is providing 52 million marks
(34.6 million U.S. dollars) to help finance reconstruction
projects in the autonomous Palestinian territories.
</P>
<P>
The German development ministry said 15 million marks (10
million dollars) of the money would be used to equip a new airport
at Gaza City and 12 million marks (eight million dollars) would be
spent on a new tourist infrastructure as well as water and garbage
treatment.
</P>
<P>
Less than half of the aid, earmarked for use in Jordan, the
West Bank and the Gaza Strip, initially was given to the Israeli
government. And the diversion of the fund use has been agreed by
the Jewish state.
</P>
<P>
The German aid package, according to officials, aims to boost
the peace process in the Middle East. 
