<HEADLINE> Spanish Foundation Supports Honduras Center </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEGUCIGALPA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A Spanish foundation has
approved help in building a cultural center in the Mosquito Coast
region of Honduras, to strengthen pre-Columbian indigenous culture.
</P>
<P>
Honduran government sources said the center would have several
lecture halls for developing intensive courses on technical and
artisan training given by national and foreign government
organizations.
</P>
<P>
The "Codespa" Foundation of Spain, presided over by the Prince
of Asturias, Felipe de Borbon, will also help build a library,
study and research rooms for students, and a printing room where
the magazine "Una Ventana al Mundo" will be published in the
"Tawaka" and "Miskito" languages and in Spanish.
</P>
<P>
The project is promoted by the Catholic Church and will support
the development of five small towns in the area whose 10,000
people live on hunting and fishing. 
