<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentines Reaches Final in Men's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Hernan Crespo scored two
second-half goals as Argentina cruised into its first Olympic
final since 1928 Tuesday with a 2-0 victory over outclassed
Portugal in Athens, Georgia.
</P>
<P>
The lanky striker, set to play for Italy's Parma next season,
headed home a cross to give Argentina the lead in the 56th minute.
And he fired a low 18-yard shot for the second six minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Portugal's Vidigal hit the post and Nuno was foiled by a reflex
save by Argentine goalkeeper Pablo Cavallero near the end. But the
South Americans deserved a victory before 78,212 fans at Stanford
Stadium.
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's final, Argentina will meet either Brazil or
Nigeria, who meet in the same stadium Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
