<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Australian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Australian
</P>
<P>
-- A plebiscite on Australia becoming a republic with a
president elected by both Houses of Parliament would be
successful, according to a latest newspoll. Of those surveyed, 54
percent supported a president elected by a two-third majority of
both houses.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald
</P>
