<HEADLINE> Japan Beats Italy 12-1 in Olympic Baseball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Makoto Imaoka's two-run homer
Tuesday clinched a 12-1 victory over Italy and sent Japan into the
medal round of the Olympic baseball tournament.
</P>
<P>
Japan, with a record of four wins and three defeats, will play
the United States (6-1) in its first medal-round game Thursday.
The United States won their round-robin meeting 15-5.
</P>
<P>
Cuba (7-0) will play Nicaragua (4-3) in the other first-round
game. The winners will play for the gold Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Italy (2-5) would have clinched the berth by beating Japan, but
couldn't get much offense. The Italians managed just six hit in
eight innings off three Japanese pitchers.
</P>
<P>
Imaoka's RBI double put Japan ahead 3-0 in the second, and
Yoshitomo Tani tripled home a run in the fourth. Japan took
control with three more runs in the fifth, which included Hideaki
Okubo's solo homer and another run-scoring double by Imaoka.
</P>
<P>
Imaoka's two-run homer with one out in the bottom of the eighth
inning invoked the 10-run rule. 
</P>
