<HEADLINE> China to Vie for Gold in Olympic Softball Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- China defeated Australia 4-2 on
Tuesday, sailing further to vie for the gold medal against host
the United States in the Olympic softball tournament.
</P>
<P>
China, runners-up in the 1994 world championship, scored its
first point through home runner Wang Ying in the second inning.
</P>
<P>
Yet, Australia, the third-place finishers in the championship,
capitalized on two receive errors of the Chinese women to overtake
the lead 2-1 for the scoreless third inning.
</P>
<P>
In the fourth inning, two hits from Liu Qing and Chen Hong
helped China to equalize the scoreboard en route to their victory.
</P>
<P>
In the fifth and seventh innings, the Chinese women scored two
more points as the Australians were betrayed by their defense.
</P>
<P>
Early in the eight-team round-robin preliminaries, China routed
Australia 6-0 in the opener of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, the United States secured the other final berth by
defeating China 1-0 in the 10th inning, while Australia won 3-0
against Japan.
</P>
<P>
Under the page system of the Olympic softball tournament, top
four squads enter the semifinals.
</P>
<P>
The winner of the first two place finishers books one final
spot, with the other to be vied between the loser and the winner
of the third and fourth place finishers.
</P>
<P>
The softball final is slated in late this evening. 
</P>
