<HEADLINE> China, Russia Enter Semifinals In Olympic Volleyball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia, which has never finished
worse than second place at the Olympics, defeated the Netherlands
3-1 on Tuesday to advance into the women's volleyball semifinals.
</P>
<P>
The Russians won 10-15, 15-7, 15-9, 15-10 to earn a semifinal
matchup with China on Thursday. China defeated Germany 15-12,
15-8, 15-8 in Tuesday's first quarterfinal.
</P>
<P>
Two other quarterfinals later Tuesday pitted the United States
against Cuba and Brazil against South Korea.
</P>
<P>
The Soviet Union won four gold and two silver medals between
1964 and 1988, missing the Los Angeles Games in 1984 because of a
boycott. The Unified Team that included athletes from the former
Soviet Union won the silver in 1992.
</P>
<P>
China beat the United States to win the gold medal at Los
Angeles in 1984, and also won the bronze in Seoul. But the Chinese
finished seventh out of eight teams in Barcelona four years ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
