<HEADLINE> Russian Lifter Strikes Weightlifting Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Russian strongman Andrey Chemerkin
set a new world jerk record on his way to take the men's over
108kg class gold medal in the final day of the Olympic
weightlifting tournament here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Chemerkin totalled 457.5kgs, 197.5kgs from snatch and 260kgs
from jerk to win the gold.
</P>
<P>
He improved the world jerk record set by Ronny Weller of
Germany a few minutes ago, and equalled the world two-lift total
record set by himself.
</P>
<P>
Weller snatched 200kgs and jerked 255kgs for a total of 455kgs
to gain the silver medal.
</P>
<P>
Weller's jerk result surpassed the listed world mark of
253.5kgs set by Chemerkin on May 7, 1995, in Warsaw of Poland.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal went to Stefan Botev of Australia who lifted a
total of 450kgs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
