<HEADLINE> New York Stock Move Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Stocks on Wall Street rallied
near the close as signs of slowing economy were revealed in
several government reports today that held out hope for modest
inflation.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 47.34 to 5,481.93, after
slipping into negative territory several times in the session.
</P>
<P>
Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by an 11-to-8 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange, with volume reaching 337.30 million
shares, up from 281.35 million in the previous light session.
</P>
<P>
The Nasdaq composite index rose 2.26 to 1,068.73, and other
major stock indexes also rose.
</P>
<P>
It is reported in the afternoon that retail sales fell from
June's levels in the first three weeks of July.
</P>
<P>
The news sent long-term interest rates lower. The yield on the
30-year Treasury bond fell to nearly 7.03 percent.
</P>
<P>
The government reported that employment costs -- a key element
of inflation -- increased 0.8 percent in the second quarter,
slightly less than expected.
</P>
<P>
The Commerce Department, meanwhile, reported that sales of new
homes slipped more than expected in June.
</P>
<P>
And even though the employment cost index fell within range of
expectations, many analysts still expect Federal Reserve policy
makers to boost short-term interest rates at their Aug. 20 meeting
to insure slower economic growth and keep inflation under control.
</P>
<P>
A private research group reported that consumer confidence
jumped in July to the highest level in six years. The report is
closely watched for the first signs of changed spending patterns by
consumers, who account for the bulk of economic growth.
</P>
</TEXT>
