<HEADLINE> Lithuania Takes on Croatia in Olympic Basketball Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATLANTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Olympic basketball silver medal
favorites Yugoslavia and Lituania will meet in the semifinals
Thursday after the two teams won their qurterfinals games with
ease here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Lithuania trounced Greece 99-66 after roaring to a 45-19
half-time lead. The Lithuanians opened the game with a 16-2 lead
with all five starters contributing.
</P>
<P>
Sarunas Marciulionis led the Lithuanians with 16 points while
Rimas Kurtinaitis and Arturas Karnisovas each added 15 points.
</P>
<P>
The Greeks were headed by Giorgos Sigalas with 18 points, and
no other players finished in double figures.
</P>
<P>
