Rentzias, who was drafted by the NBA Denver Nuggets earlier in
June.
</P>
<P>
"Our defense was not strong and we weren't very aggressive in
our offense. So I can't say that Lithuania is a better team than
us; we just didn't play well today," he said.
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's second quarterfinaL, Group A winner Yugoslavia
overwhelmed Gruop A fourth placer China 128-61. The 67 winning
margin is the biggest since the basketball tournament started on
July 20.
</P>
<P>
"It's a record for us to enter the first eight in the Olympic
Games," Chinese head coach Gong Luming said. "Everyone was
complacent because of this and they didn't play well."
</P>
<P>
China will face Greece Thursday in the play-off with the winner
entering the 5th to 6th places.
</P>
<P>
Yugolavia will face its toughest rival Lithurania in the
Olympic Games in the semifinals Thursday but team captain Zarko
Paspalj thought it will be a difficult game because Yugoslavia
headed into the semifinals without so much competitive games.
</P>
<P>
"We were nervous in our first Olympic game against Greece and
the competition format does not give us the opportunity to prepare
for a good team although in the group you won by 30,40 or 50
points," said Paspalj.
</P>
<P>
"You don't know what you really do against an equal opponent.
It is good that we know Lithuania is the same as we are. And it'll
be a very hard game," he added. 
</P>
